<subSubSection id="5BD4E89AD973BB8E2DB9016DD724F07E" pageId="null" pageNumber="599" type="vernacular_names">
<paragraph id="641F12D6F5CA70588C924017789F561A" pageId="null" pageNumber="599">Nestwurz</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</title>
<subSubSection id="2076356CD75414030FAF1FB25BFFD09C" pageId="null" pageNumber="599" type="description">
<paragraph id="EB80DC4C07C45C3AF7D0AF0655CBDBE2" pageId="null" pageNumber="599">
Rhizom kriechend; die fleischigen Seitenwurzeln ein dichtes, 
<normalizedToken id="5493FEF0CD9D8372A44E7334867D4AFE" originalValue="nestähnliches" pageId="null" pageNumber="599">nestaehnliches</normalizedToken>
Geflecht bildend. 
<emphasis id="926EA72C195B3ED0DC04D86E70492E35" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="599">
Pflanze ohne 
<normalizedToken id="AA5BD3ED25DE27FF4863CF480E1B7C42" originalValue="Blattgrün" pageId="null" pageNumber="599">Blattgruen</normalizedToken>
, hellbraun.
</emphasis>
5 
<normalizedToken id="54FF3AB532553DB6546E45923BB05AB4" originalValue="Perigonblätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="599">Perigonblaetter</normalizedToken>
zusammenneigend; 
<emphasis id="E5304501892301D050B948011FD4C973" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="599">Lippe am Grunde sackartig vertieft; kein Sporn.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D88268F93C75E836149F402B932925C9" pageId="null" pageNumber="599">
<pageBreakToken id="4474C70D9E803E06544FF09EAF147172" pageId="null" pageNumber="599">Die</pageBreakToken>
Gattung 
<taxonomicName id="0665C85B80AD6CA88A668704C9A28A93" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Neottia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="null" pageNumber="599" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="77C3540CB21F80C7A3365AA6247F89A1" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="599">Neottia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="6B0E13FA0B59295C8EEBB3C77E634A8F" originalValue="umfaßt" pageId="null" pageNumber="599">umfasst</normalizedToken>
<emphasis id="61AD2B4F91F3F7427F2F469E8784BED3" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="599">9 Arten;</emphasis>
Zentrum der Gattung ist das 
<emphasis id="3DAAB3F9E49D81FFDC04E2E9F2ED0611" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="599">Himalajagebiet und Ostasien;</emphasis>
in 
<taxonomicName id="2DD752152CF33ABBEAF337687FD07385" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Europa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="null" pageNumber="599" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Europa</taxonomicName>
nur 1 Art; in Nordamerika ist die Gattung nicht vorhanden. Die Gattung 
<taxonomicName id="35EB2EB149C8228DBABC6EB6DF339677" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Neottia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="null" pageNumber="599" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7F9BB58FC1F34D9B2536D946CB8B1451" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="599">Neottia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
ist mit der Gattung 
<taxonomicName id="94C183C054D418BCA009CE8B0123A323" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Listera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="null" pageNumber="599" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="BE140F44AB053B84245B6D80076DBBAE" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="599">Listera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
verwandt. Die 
<taxonomicName id="0501B206BEF96CFBACBEEB28E488AA3C" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Neottia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="null" pageNumber="599" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C2A5ECDE127C2568A7DBABADE5A97DEE" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="599">Neottia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
arten leben alle saprophytisch auf moderndem Holz.
</paragraph>
